25:37.136 --> 25:38.501
- Tueli!

25:38.538 --> 25:40.371
- Oh, kelly. Hey.
- Sup.

25:40.506 --> 25:41.572
- Hey. Hi.
- Hi.

25:41.641 --> 25:43.707
- Hi, there you are. Hi.

25:43.842 --> 25:47.177
Hi. Ugh, you know,
I've been buzzing,

25:47.246 --> 25:49.012
Buzzing,
thinking you were home.

25:49.081 --> 25:52.849
Uh, normally somebody passes
and let's me in but not today.

25:53.553 --> 25:54.651
Pointless, right? Yeah.

25:54.720 --> 25:57.121
Um, I lost my keycard
so I was just kind of hoping

25:57.123 --> 25:58.589
Someone would show up.

25:58.591 --> 26:01.091
- Right. Right.

26:01.127 --> 26:04.461
Well, here I am.
- Thank you.

26:04.497 --> 26:05.829
- Mm-hmm.

26:15.341 --> 26:17.674
- Open...
- Ugh, I'm opening it.

26:18.744 --> 26:20.678
(all): Surprise!

26:21.914 --> 26:25.616
- Oh, wow, I am so blown away.

26:25.751 --> 26:29.486
What a surprise!
- You had no idea, right?

26:29.488 --> 26:33.089
Fooled you.
- Yeah... You sure did.

26:33.125 --> 26:34.825
- You need a ladies' night
to celebrate.

26:34.894 --> 26:36.760
Oh, karina couldn't be here,
she's at home with brixy,

26:36.796 --> 26:38.162
He's got a cold.
- Okay.

26:38.297 --> 26:39.896
- But, I have another surprise
for you.

26:39.932 --> 26:42.499
- What? Let me guess,
a stripper?

26:42.535 --> 26:44.568
- She was really glad
we invited her.

26:44.703 --> 26:48.572
- You got me a girl? Ooh--
- congratulations, honey!

26:48.574 --> 26:52.976
Oh, I haven't seen you
in such a long time.

26:52.979 --> 26:56.446
Come on, you don't have a hug
for your old mama?

26:58.684 --> 27:00.050
- Wow...

27:00.052 --> 27:03.019
You guys know how to knock me
on my ass, don't you?

27:03.055 --> 27:04.521
- You know I don't do parties,
right?

27:04.590 --> 27:06.857
But I just had to come and
celebrate the fact

27:06.859 --> 27:08.726
That you finally found yourself
a good man.

27:08.861 --> 27:11.395
And he found himself
a great woman, come on!

27:11.464 --> 27:13.831
- I really appreciate it,
I really do.

27:13.833 --> 27:17.467
I see you all have met my mom,
donna, I guess.

27:17.503 --> 27:21.038
- She has kept us in stitches
for the last half-hour.

27:21.107 --> 27:24.007
She was telling us stories
about you and your sisters.

27:24.043 --> 27:26.143
(laughing)

27:26.145 --> 27:27.944
- I bet. Sorry I missed it.

27:27.980 --> 27:31.215
Um, I need a drink,

27:31.350 --> 27:32.649
So, I'll be right back.

27:33.285 --> 27:34.284
Continue the party.

27:34.286 --> 27:37.287
(laughing)
- well, back to me.

27:37.423 --> 27:39.089
(laughing)

27:39.091 --> 27:40.791
Now, you think I've been
sharing stories?

27:40.926 --> 27:43.626
Girl, I have not told you
anything yet.

27:43.663 --> 27:45.295
You gotta get comfortable.

27:45.431 --> 27:47.297
Awhere did I put my drink?
Where's my drink?

27:47.299 --> 27:49.833
- Here, it's over here.
- There you go. Okay.

27:49.968 --> 27:52.269
(overlapping chatter)

27:56.108 --> 27:56.973
- Yeah...

27:59.945 --> 28:01.678
Alright. I win.

28:02.748 --> 28:04.081
Now talk.

28:04.216 --> 28:05.249
Hurry up.

28:05.985 --> 28:07.417
I'm not feeling so good.

28:08.253 --> 28:10.521
- Oh my god, I love this song!

28:10.656 --> 28:12.789
(muffled music)

28:13.959 --> 28:16.193
- Man, I can't handle
drinking like I used to.

28:16.195 --> 28:17.261
(sighs)

28:17.396 --> 28:19.329
- Yeah, man.
That's not the booze.

28:19.331 --> 28:21.531
It's probably the purple rain
I slipped into your drink

28:21.600 --> 28:23.333
A while ago.

28:23.335 --> 28:24.334
- What?!

28:24.870 --> 28:25.669
Are you...

28:26.272 --> 28:27.671
Are you serious?

28:27.673 --> 28:30.140
- Yeah, man. I'm dead serious.

28:30.910 --> 28:32.209
It's gonna be a trip.

28:34.113 --> 28:35.212
Whew!

28:35.281 --> 28:36.746
Ha, ha, ha!

28:38.718 --> 28:40.217
(rhythmic music)

28:41.754 --> 28:43.487
(breathing deeply)

28:47.093 --> 28:48.892
(laughing)
- I never thought I'd

28:48.928 --> 28:52.428
See the day when
this one got married.

28:53.699 --> 28:56.567
I remember kelly heading off
to school some Halloween,

28:56.702 --> 28:59.102
Must have been about
second grade.

28:59.105 --> 29:02.372
She was dressed as wonder woman.
(all): Aw.

29:02.441 --> 29:03.907
- She was wearing one
of my wigs,

29:04.042 --> 29:06.310
Big cape made out of
a garbage bag,

29:06.312 --> 29:08.178
And I said to her, I said,

29:08.214 --> 29:11.381
"why did you pick wonder woman?"

29:11.383 --> 29:12.682
You know what she said?

29:14.453 --> 29:18.655
Cool bracelet, fights bad guys,

29:18.691 --> 29:21.191
Never has to get married.

29:21.260 --> 29:22.826
(cheering)

29:25.063 --> 29:27.864
- Right. Is that before you went
on that trip to cancun

29:27.933 --> 29:31.201
For a week then didn't come back
for two months?

29:32.104 --> 29:34.938
- You are right. You are right.

29:34.940 --> 29:38.208
I started interning at a little
pottery shop

29:38.244 --> 29:40.143
I stumbled onto.

29:40.146 --> 29:43.913
I was very caught up in finding
myself back then.

29:45.151 --> 29:49.052
But here I was, all along.

29:52.224 --> 29:52.956
(clears throat)

29:54.260 --> 29:57.460
- So, um, speaking of
wonder woman,

29:57.530 --> 30:02.365
Uh, did you know that
the creator also invented
the polygraph?

30:02.401 --> 30:03.700
(gasping)
- no!

30:03.836 --> 30:04.968
- Yeah, yeah.

30:05.103 --> 30:06.904
And a bit of a non sequitur,

30:06.906 --> 30:09.239
He was also into bondage
and submission.

30:09.308 --> 30:11.575
(laughing)
- fascinating.

30:11.644 --> 30:14.578
Gloria, are you married?
- Me?

30:14.647 --> 30:17.514
Oh. No. I've never really
seen the point.

30:17.649 --> 30:22.385
For me, it only became, um,
legal in 2005.

30:22.421 --> 30:25.054
- Respect. I am with you.

30:25.691 --> 30:27.357
I mean, I love men.

30:28.160 --> 30:29.459
And women.

30:31.363 --> 30:33.730
But I wouldn't want
to be married to any of 'em.

30:33.766 --> 30:36.066
(laughing)
am I right?

30:36.201 --> 30:37.568
- You are right!

30:37.703 --> 30:39.670
- This was a really,
really bad idea.

30:39.672 --> 30:41.137
- Kelly, relax.

30:41.173 --> 30:43.073
Live a little, forgive a little.

30:43.075 --> 30:45.141
She's not the same person
she was when we were kids.

30:45.211 --> 30:48.211
Why don't you take five minutes
to find that out for yourself.

30:50.148 --> 30:51.548
(sighs)

31:01.560 --> 31:03.426
- Are you sure she's not
going to mind?

31:03.495 --> 31:05.562
- Yeah, kelly said, "bring ro".

31:05.697 --> 31:07.631
And then she said my friends
are her friends.

31:07.633 --> 31:09.632
You know, ro,
and your friends are my friends,

31:09.668 --> 31:12.903
So guess what?
That makes all of us friends.

31:13.038 --> 31:14.905
- Ro thinks I spend too much
time talking to fish

31:14.974 --> 31:16.907
And not enough time talking
to humans, so.

31:17.042 --> 31:18.241
- I do think that.

31:19.444 --> 31:20.710
- Your friends like tequila?

31:20.746 --> 31:22.012
- Who doesn't?

31:25.751 --> 31:27.116
(buzzing)

31:30.556 --> 31:32.188
- I appreciate you inviting her.

31:32.224 --> 31:35.191
I'm the only person she has
in the world and it's just...

31:35.227 --> 31:37.760
It's a lot sometimes.
- Oh my gosh, no problem.

31:38.731 --> 31:39.863
Let's get in there
and have some fun.

31:39.932 --> 31:41.064
- Alright.
- Yeah.

31:41.199 --> 31:42.132
- Yeah.

31:43.602 --> 31:46.136
(overlapping chatter)

31:46.138 --> 31:48.438
- Hi.
- Hello!

31:48.507 --> 31:49.606
- Ah! Welcome!

31:49.675 --> 31:51.275
Come in! Come in.

31:53.345 --> 31:55.412
- Jenn, don't be shy.
Come on.

31:56.682 --> 31:58.482
Kelly, oh my god.
Congratulations.

31:58.617 --> 32:00.683
It's so great,
I'm so happy for you.

32:00.719 --> 32:02.819
- Oh, thank you so much, ro.

32:02.821 --> 32:05.355
Bit last minute, but so glad
you could make it.

32:05.490 --> 32:07.791
I'm sorry, you are?
- Jenn.

32:07.926 --> 32:10.026
Diamante. We were having
a taco night

32:10.095 --> 32:11.828
And then the next thing I know,
here we are.

32:11.830 --> 32:13.530
- Is that prometida tequila?

32:13.599 --> 32:16.700
- Yes, ma'am, my favourite.
You wanna do shots with me?

32:16.702 --> 32:18.635
- Please, yes.

32:18.704 --> 32:20.570
(laughing)
- oh my gosh,

32:20.639 --> 32:22.672
I feel that headache
coming on.

32:23.909 --> 32:27.077
- Uh, these are my bosses.
This is ro wells.

32:27.146 --> 32:29.246
Uh, she works with steve
at the firm.

32:29.381 --> 32:32.716
- Wow, a defence lawyer.
- Usually, but not tonight.

32:32.718 --> 32:33.750
- Good.

32:33.786 --> 32:35.385
- Tonight, I'm here celebrating
friendship.

32:35.520 --> 32:38.654
- Oh, isn't that nice?
- Okay, let me get you a drink.

32:38.691 --> 32:41.258
- Yes, friend. Please.

32:41.393 --> 32:44.194
- So you're the friend
that works in the aquarium
store, right?

32:44.196 --> 32:46.196
- That's me.
- Is there a lot of money

32:46.265 --> 32:47.797
In that line of business, or...

32:47.833 --> 32:49.266
(chuckling)
- why?

32:49.401 --> 32:50.734
You looking to switch careers?

32:50.736 --> 32:53.036
- Hey, it's always
a possibility, right?

32:53.605 --> 32:54.971
- What?

32:54.974 --> 32:57.407
Your job's way more exciting
than mine,

32:57.476 --> 32:59.810
Busting big, bad, drug dealers.

32:59.945 --> 33:02.079
- Sounds more fun than it is.

33:02.081 --> 33:04.214
You know, most drug dealers
are just people

33:04.283 --> 33:05.816
Who ended up on the wrong path.

33:05.951 --> 33:08.017
- That's very compassionate
of you.

33:08.053 --> 33:10.087
Not a typical cop,
I take it.

33:10.089 --> 33:11.288
- No.

33:11.423 --> 33:14.157
I try not to be.
- Stop! No! Wait!

33:14.193 --> 33:15.993
Halt for me, me... I join.

33:16.128 --> 33:17.727
Okay, here we go.

33:18.397 --> 33:19.429
Thank you.
(sighs)

33:19.564 --> 33:22.099
Alright!
- Ladies.

33:22.101 --> 33:25.034
- Uh-uh-uh.

33:25.070 --> 33:26.236
- Uh.

33:27.039 --> 33:28.238
- Mm.

33:28.907 --> 33:31.041
- Mm.
- Uh--

33:31.176 --> 33:32.776
- Mm...

33:32.845 --> 33:35.111
- That'll get
the party started. Mm.

33:36.382 --> 33:38.014
- I'll go share them around.

33:38.050 --> 33:39.516
- My eyes are watering.

33:39.651 --> 33:40.850
Ugh.

33:42.688 --> 33:44.788
Did you get anything out of her?

33:44.857 --> 33:46.456
- No. I'm still feeling her out.

33:46.525 --> 33:48.592
Plus, I am grateful
for anything to distract me

33:48.594 --> 33:50.993
From the guest
I was surprised with.

33:51.030 --> 33:52.362
- What happened?
Did tueli invite her mother?

33:52.364 --> 33:53.797
- No, adriana brought mine.

33:53.866 --> 33:55.732
- That's your mother?
- Yes, that's mine.

33:56.468 --> 33:58.468
(soft music)

33:59.471 --> 34:01.071
(soft groaning)

34:05.343 --> 34:06.876
- Whoa.

34:07.746 --> 34:08.878
(sighs)

34:13.152 --> 34:15.852
- Oh gosh. Oh gosh.

34:17.623 --> 34:18.821
Oh no.

34:19.425 --> 34:21.224
Oh no, buddy.

34:22.661 --> 34:23.960
Buddy.

34:24.630 --> 34:26.096
I gave you too much.

34:26.765 --> 34:27.830
Yeah.

34:28.634 --> 34:30.833
You're doing the zombie thing.

34:31.403 --> 34:32.836
Relax. Relax...

34:34.540 --> 34:35.438
It'll pass.

34:38.010 --> 34:39.308
Guess what?

34:40.045 --> 34:41.511
I'm leaving town.

34:42.748 --> 34:45.648
Costa rica is awesome, hm?

34:46.685 --> 34:48.118
Maybe a little obvious.

34:48.987 --> 34:52.121
Yeah, maybe ecuador?

34:52.691 --> 34:54.324
Panama?

34:54.459 --> 34:58.929
Tree house in the forest,
hunker down and just...

35:01.233 --> 35:02.866
Makes you sharp--
- I see you.

35:02.935 --> 35:04.367
- You can see things.

35:04.436 --> 35:07.170
I... See you.

35:07.673 --> 35:09.139
- I see you.

35:09.141 --> 35:10.740
- Hey naz.

35:11.977 --> 35:15.879
Easy, naz. Watch out, naz.
Check it out.

35:16.014 --> 35:17.948
I got a vision, naz.
- Don't.

35:18.083 --> 35:20.016
(chuckles)
- trust me.

35:20.152 --> 35:21.451
- Don't!

35:24.222 --> 35:25.622
(chuckling)

35:26.992 --> 35:28.291
- See?

35:29.961 --> 35:31.994
It's making
the real you come out.

35:32.965 --> 35:34.097
You're strong.

35:34.232 --> 35:35.899
You're tough.

35:35.968 --> 35:37.234
- I don't like this, jake.

35:39.104 --> 35:40.770
I don't like this at all.

35:41.573 --> 35:44.440
- It's okay, man. It's okay.

35:44.476 --> 35:47.911
Now listen. I gotta get this
for posterity.

35:47.980 --> 35:49.779
(chuckling)

35:49.781 --> 35:51.982
Hi, nazeer,

35:51.984 --> 35:55.118
Off his head
on purple rain.

35:55.120 --> 35:56.586
- Stop! Stop!

35:56.721 --> 35:58.588
- Your cop pals
are gonna love it.

35:58.723 --> 36:01.191
(laughing)
- biggest cocaine arrest

36:01.326 --> 36:05.361
In canadian history,
the mastermind right here,

36:05.363 --> 36:07.197
This woman right here.

36:07.332 --> 36:09.465
- Oh, come on now,
it was nothing.

36:09.535 --> 36:11.935
Look, it was just five guys
sitting around

36:12.004 --> 36:13.136
Picking their asses.

36:13.138 --> 36:16.673
All it took is one woman
with an opinion.

36:16.742 --> 36:18.141
- A big opinion.
- Well--

36:18.276 --> 36:19.342
- Yeah.

36:19.477 --> 36:22.279
- How much product?
- Ooh. How much product.

36:22.414 --> 36:24.547
- I've seen the wire,
I know the lingo.

36:24.583 --> 36:26.149
- Oh, come on, ro,
you must have defended

36:26.284 --> 36:27.617
Big drug dealers before.

36:27.619 --> 36:29.051
- You know I don't
kiss and tell.

36:29.087 --> 36:32.289
But if you women had
a hand in bringing them down,

36:32.291 --> 36:33.957
There's no way I would have
stood a chance

36:34.092 --> 36:35.758
At getting them off.
- Well, that's funny,

36:35.794 --> 36:37.594
Because you got a crackerjack
lawyer at your firm

36:37.729 --> 36:40.496
Who found a way to get
our whole case thrown out.

36:40.532 --> 36:41.831
- Oh, that case was yours?

36:42.801 --> 36:44.701
We've had these geniuses
coming to us

36:44.703 --> 36:46.169
Right out of law school
these days.

36:46.238 --> 36:48.238
- Oh, what law school? I'm
thinking of going to law school.

36:48.307 --> 36:49.706
- Oh, what about policing?

36:49.775 --> 36:51.041
- You know, I thought
about policing,

36:51.176 --> 36:53.576
But not now that I have a baby.
- Why not?

36:53.579 --> 36:55.312
(overlapping chatter)
- she's a mother--

36:55.447 --> 36:58.381
- Okay, you know what?
Let's not forget why we're here,

36:58.417 --> 37:00.082
To cheers, kelly.

37:01.386 --> 37:04.120
Congratulations on your
not so very secret engagement.

37:04.256 --> 37:06.055
(cheering)

37:10.162 --> 37:14.264
- Okay, okay. I would like to--

37:14.266 --> 37:18.001
- Oh, I love this song! Ugh!

37:18.070 --> 37:20.136
(laughing)

37:20.205 --> 37:23.807
I cannot hear this song
and not move!

37:23.942 --> 37:26.243
- Mom, we can't talk
when the music is so loud.

37:26.378 --> 37:30.413
- Then don't talk, dance.
Come on!

37:30.482 --> 37:32.948
(cheering)

37:32.985 --> 37:35.351
(overlapping chatter)

37:41.192 --> 37:43.760
(hip-hop music)

38:00.445 --> 38:02.512
(grunting)

38:02.514 --> 38:04.014
(screaming)

38:06.952 --> 38:09.018
(panting)

38:10.122 --> 38:12.255
- Whoa, so cute.

38:12.390 --> 38:13.723
- It's a goby fish.

38:13.725 --> 38:15.825
I got it with jenn.
We were what, 16?

38:16.995 --> 38:18.728
- Mm-hmm.
- She's the goby, not me.

38:18.797 --> 38:21.030
- Show me yours.
- Ugh, no. That's okay.

38:21.066 --> 38:23.366
- She's the pistol shrimp.
They're best buddies.

38:23.368 --> 38:25.134
- Like, symbiotic?

38:26.571 --> 38:28.070
(both): Mutualistic.

38:28.106 --> 38:29.605
- Jinx, buy me a coke.

38:29.607 --> 38:31.341
Show your tattoo. Do it.
- Ugh.

38:34.646 --> 38:37.480
Yeah, mutualism is the highest
form of symbiosis

38:37.615 --> 38:39.014
Because, um, well, it's...

38:39.051 --> 38:40.617
- Both parties' benefit.

38:40.752 --> 38:43.920
- Goby and the shrimp,
they bond as juveniles

38:44.055 --> 38:45.822
And then they stay together
their entire lives.

38:45.957 --> 38:47.623
Just like me and jenn.

38:48.293 --> 38:49.359
(knocking)

38:49.361 --> 38:50.426
- I'll get it.

38:50.495 --> 38:51.594
- Yeah, thank you.

38:55.233 --> 38:57.199
- I'm here.
- Yes, please.

39:02.907 --> 39:04.174
- I have new--
- no, I know...

39:04.176 --> 39:05.641
- Purple rain--
- no, shh, stop,

39:05.643 --> 39:07.844
'cause we have to do it
in there. Okay? Oh, god.

39:09.181 --> 39:12.047
- I'm here with new information
on the purple rain case.

39:13.251 --> 39:15.684
- What are you doing?
- It's about the informant.

39:15.721 --> 39:18.788
- I don't care, not at my
engagement party, give me this!

39:18.790 --> 39:21.791
Put it on my desk upstairs
and deal with it later, come on.

39:22.594 --> 39:25.294
(indistinct chatter)

39:38.209 --> 39:42.145
- I gotta get her home,
she's had way too much tequila.

39:42.214 --> 39:43.913
- I'm gonna throw up.
- Wow.

39:44.048 --> 39:45.681
Okay. Uh, where's your bathroom?

39:45.751 --> 39:48.151
- There's one that way
or upstairs, please.

39:48.153 --> 39:49.485
- I'm just gonna take
her upstairs

39:49.554 --> 39:51.020
Because this is already
embarrassing enough,

39:51.156 --> 39:53.356
You don't need to see her
hurl her guts.

39:53.358 --> 39:55.224
Come on. There you go,
there you go.

39:56.361 --> 39:58.294
- What are you two guys up to?

39:58.330 --> 40:00.697
(both): What are you
talking about?

40:00.699 --> 40:03.166
- I am not ready
to shut this night down,

40:03.168 --> 40:05.168
Let's open another bottle.
- No--

40:05.237 --> 40:06.903
- I gotta go to bed,
I'm so sleepy.

40:06.905 --> 40:09.105
- Okay, maybe we can go
find a drink somewhere else.

40:09.240 --> 40:10.273
- Yeah!
- Come on.

40:10.342 --> 40:13.309
- That's a good idea!
- Tomorrow is another day.

40:13.445 --> 40:15.912
Excelsior!

40:16.047 --> 40:17.313
Come on!

40:17.916 --> 40:19.449
- My baby...

40:19.584 --> 40:22.084
Mm, my baby.
- Yeah.

40:24.256 --> 40:26.255
